Juniper has already made it through the most dangerous part of her emergency, but this is where many families still feel the pressure. Recovery care, monitoring, medications, and discharge planning all cost money after the surgery itself.

## Why in-treatment matters

An in-treatment case shows the work after the initial emergency. This is the stretch where families are relieved, exhausted, and still dealing with bills that determine what happens next.

## What the remaining goal covers

The remaining amount will support post-op monitoring, medications, follow-up imaging, and the care plan that helps Juniper transition safely back home.
